  "text": "Neutrophil activation is required for NADPH oxidase assembly and surface expression of CD11b/CD18, required for adhesion of neutrophils to endothelial cells during inflammatory responses, is an established marker of neutrophil activation [CITATION_1] . To see whether any difference in activation was apparent, CD11b and CD18 surface expression was measured on neutrophils from BAL. Neutrophils from gp91 phox2/-mice showed greater activation than those from C57BL/6 mice, with higher levels of CD11b ( Figure 6A ) and CD18 surface expression ( Figure 6B ). In addition, there was lower surface expression of CD62L on neutrophils from gp91 phox2/-mice, as compared with those from C57BL/6 mice after infection, in keeping with Figure 2 . Reduced bacteria in lung and blood from gp91 phox2/-mice after high-dose pneumococcal infection. Bacteria in (A) lung homogenates and (B) blood from wild-type C57BL/6 control mice and gp91 phox2/-mice were determined 24 hours after intratracheal instillation of 10 7 cfu of type 2 pneumococci. Means and SEM, MannWhitney. a significant increase in the shedding of CD62L and enhanced activation ( Figure 6C ). These findings suggested that reduced susceptibility to apoptosis was not associated with decreased activation.",
